Factory Assistant is based on Home Assistant.

This repository provides industrial monitoring add-ons for Factory Assistant,
built to run on the Home Assistant Supervisor / add-on platform developed by
the Home Assistant project (https://www.home-assistant.io/), licensed under
the Apache License, Version 2.0. The Home Assistant add-on contract (the
`config.yaml` schema and the add-on base images this repository builds FROM)
is used unchanged so that community add-ons remain compatible.

"Home Assistant" and the Home Assistant logo are trademarks of their
respective owners (the Home Assistant project / Open Home Foundation). The
name is used here solely for factual attribution of origin, as permitted for
describing the origin of the Work. Factory Assistant is an independent project
and is not affiliated with or endorsed by the Home Assistant project, the Open
Home Foundation, or Nabu Casa, Inc.

These add-ons are monitoring tools and are READ-ONLY by default. They must not
be configured or relied upon for machine control, emergency stop, interlock,
or any safety-rated function. See the Factory Assistant safety boundary
(docs/SAFETY_BOUNDARY.md in the factory-assistant OS repository).

Individual add-ons bundle third-party open source components under their own
licenses, retained in the corresponding container images and source trees:

  - opcua-mqtt-bridge: asyncua (LGPL-3.0), paho-mqtt (EPL-2.0 / EDL-1.0),
    PyYAML (MIT), and the Home Assistant add-on base image.
  - historian: the InfluxDB / Telegraf client tooling referenced in DOCS.md,
    each under its own upstream license.
  - node-red: wraps the community Node-RED add-on and the Node-RED project
    (Apache-2.0), which carry their own NOTICE/attribution.
